{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix imscope recording thread race condition in dumpScopeData function\n\n### Summary\nThe `dumpScopeData` function in the imscope recording module has a race condition that prevents subsequent scope data dumps after the first one. This occurs because the shared `void_instruction` variable gets corrupted when `compare_exchange_weak` fails, causing all future dump requests to be ignored.\n\nWhen users attempt to trigger multiple scope recordings during a session (e.g., after PDSCH decoding errors, then after PUSCH errors), only the first dump request succeeds. Subsequent requests silently fail, making debugging difficult. Users observe that the imscope-dump directory only contains the first recorded file, even when multiple dump triggers are expected.\n\nThe fix ensures each call to `dumpScopeData` uses a fresh expected value for comparison, preventing corruption of the shared void instruction state.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/imscope/imscope_record.cpp`: Modified `dumpScopeData` function to create a fresh `expected` variable with default values `{-1, -1, nullptr}` for each `compare_exchange_weak` call, instead of reusing the shared `void_instruction` variable.\n"
}